result.name: MO Bar

reviews.text: The MO bar is part of the Landmark Mandarin Oriental. While the setting is nice and relaxing for a post-dinner drink, I find that they skimp on the alcohol here. A "Bite the Bullet" cocktail was HKD168, on the more expensive ranges of cocktails, and was not very strong at all. Yes, I could still taste the alcohol, but I didn't pay this much for a watered down drink. My friends also felt the same as well for their drinks. The "Kentucky Melt" was even weaker than my drink! Unbelievable.
Snacks are quite good. Drinks are slightly too sweet tho

Good value Sunday brunch at the chic bar of Landmark Mandarin. Casual & yet refined brunch with good choices of starters, main courses, side dishes & desserts. Free flow of champagne, wines & drinks are included. If one has skipped breakfast & comes for brunch, food portions are so generous to fill any hungry stomach.
Nice and cosy. Excellent place to unwind with a drink!

Great place to hang out and mingle.

Decor is chic but not TOO gaudy.  Love how they have setup a huge mirror above the bar area at 45-degree angle so you can see exactly what poison they are concocting.

Drinks are excellent as expected; finger foods ranges from average (nachos with cheese and salsa), to above average (for their "tower", with a jar of foie gras).

result.formatted_address: 15 Queen's Road Central, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: The Landmark, Mandarin Oriental

reviews.text: I have stayed at this hotel with family twice now . Ir is by far the best hotel  we have stated in ever. The service is top notch . They  think  of everything to make your stay more comfortable . From fruit bowl and fresh pastries  face masks, foot spray all sorts of little touches which we appreciate. The spa is one of the best in any hotel. We had massages and facials all top quality . We will continue to be repeat clients in this hotel.

We stayed in this establishment 4 months ago with family. The hotel is expensive, but to compare the hotels we have stayed since (8+) The Landmark is still the best hotel we have been in. The service from walking in the front door is spot on. Its not just service with a smile, it's the genuine nature of all the staff who assisted us proactively.    Waylon and staff service A++ (any parent would be proud with an A+ :P) you guys/gals are unreal. not sure if its the training you were given, or just the experiences you have developed over years. I couldn't fault it. Rooms and Food is massive tick. Location of the hotel is perfect. shop,food,party,transport all within 100m walking distance. Hope to see the same crew when I return one day.

K & N

A sumptuous 5 star hotel. We just had lunch here and the cuisine was impressive. We cannot comment on the rooms as we didn't stay here. The food was exquisite and delicious. The price we finally paid was bewildering.

5 stars hotel indeed! the staffs here are super friendly and supreme service! the room is nice. the location is perfect for all kind of tourists or business men. 24hrs in-room dining and service. i would say it’s one of the best hotel that i have stayed. i would love to stay here again. kudos to all staffs here.
Upscale swanky hotel connected to a large mall. Neila went above and beyond in helping me get to know the area and provided some super helpful tips.

result.formatted_address: 5 Connaught Rd Central, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Mandarin Oriental, Hong Kong

reviews.text: 5 stars hotel indeed! the staffs here are super friendly and supreme service! the room is nice. the location is perfect for all kind of tourists or business men. 24hrs in-room dining and service. i would say it’s one of the best hotel that i have stayed. i would love to stay here again. I left my phone in the taxi, with the help of staff and the police station near the hotel, I found it by end of the day. Thank you so much. Highly recommended.

Amazing full service hotel! If you want personal and incredible service be sure to stay here! Miranda Chan was incredibly and provided the best customer service I’ve ever experienced! What a wonderful stay!!! Thank you
Beautiful hotel with a luxurious scent. Came here for a coffee meeting. Wonderful customer service. Would love to stay one day.

Always love Mandarin Oriental. In Hong Kong, the hotel room was nice and of a good size. Beds are always comfy. The ice bucket was well selected. The vanity in front of the bathroom was well designed. The shower was nice and powerful. Room service was also delicious. I loved the fact that; for example, once you leave your glasses in the bedroom, then during room cleaning, you’ll receive a piece of cloth put next to your glasses.

Relatively small hotel with gorgeous modern, comfortable rooms furnished to a high standard. It was also very clean and relatively spacious for Hong Kong. Breakfast was delightful. Access was good with shops, amenities, and the subway a stones throw away. 

Obviously it comes at a high price, so I would usually only stay here on special occasions.

result.name: 香港文華東方酒店

reviews.text: 自助餐👍👍👍

アフタヌーンティーで利用しました。
料理はもちろん美味しいですし、接客もいき届いており気持ちよく利用できました。

お土産で購入した薔薇のジャムはとても薫りよく程よい甘さがたまりません。
紅茶にスプーン一杯入れるのがお薦めです。

5 stars hotel indeed! the staffs here are super friendly and supreme service! the room is nice. the location is perfect for all kind of tourists or business men. 24hrs in-room dining and service. i would say it’s one of the best hotel that i have stayed. i would love to stay here again. I left my phone in the taxi, with the help of staff and the police station near the hotel, I found it by end of the day. Thank you so much. Highly recommended.

立地、ホスピタリティ溢れるサービス、設備のクオリティの高さ。どれをとっても素晴らしい。

チェックイン前、チェックアウト後も荷物は預かってくれるので気軽にお出かけができる。

1階のバーは混み合っていたが、最上階のバーは比較的空いてる印象。トリュフ風味のナッツが最高に美味しかった。売ってくれないかな。

飯店實在是非常好，雖住過不少5星級與以上的飯店，但香港文華東方(舊的)真的非常棒，除了高級之外，風格非常典雅與藝術，一樓大廳有正面牆的木雕，刻工精緻，一樓大廳座位舒服，而且每幾天會換上不同花卉裝飾。整間飯店充蠻甜甜香水味，但不刺鼻，空調讓空氣流通好。走道、酒吧、房間內的各個地方，細節好仔細好美。在寸土寸金的香港，房間算很大的，衛浴空間很大，洗澡間與廁所分開，使用方便，電視下的櫃子以皮件包覆，櫃子充滿機關，各面都可打開，裡面有紅酒、香檳、、氣泡水零食、酒杯、開瓶器……等。不用插卡取電，電、燈都是用按鈕控制，光是研究這些機關就很好玩。咖啡機、冰塊盒、茶、咖啡等基本配備當然都有。飯店豪華又典雅，住宿一晚大約4000多港幣。
